What:		/sys/devices/platform/*.usb_phy/dp_tune/<rate>/vs_<vs>/pe_<pe>/<coeff>
Date:		April, 2025
Contact:	"RD Babiera" <rdbabiera@google.com>
Description:
		These files are used to adjust the DPTX tuning parameters on the USB PHY driver.
        <rate> is one of [rbr, hbr, hbr2, hbr3]. vs, or voltage swing, has valid
        values of [0,3]. pe, or pre-emphasis level, has valid values of [0,3], where
        vs + pe is less than 4. The coefficients are [main, pre, post], where each
        coefficient is a tap in the TX equalizer.

        Each of these nodes are rw. The read value reflects the current PHY
        driver override table value, and are applied during DisplayPort link
        training. Writes are presistent for the lifetime of the platform device,
        and should be performed prior to establishing the link. The values are
        only applied if dp_tune_ovrd_en is enabled.

What:		/sys/kernel/debug/google_usb_phy/tx_eq/lane*/<coeff>
Date:		April, 2025
Contact:	"RD Babiera" <rdbabiera@google.com>
Description:
		These files are used to read the live TX EQ values through ASIC on the
        USB PHY driver. USB or DisplayPort is expected to be active in order for
        the read to function. lane* ranges from lane0 to lane3, and coeff is one
        of [main, pre, post].

        These nodes are read only.

What:		/sys/module/google_usb_phy/parameters/dp_tune_ovrd_en
Date:		April, 2025
Contact:	"RD Babiera" <rdbabiera@google.com>
Description:
		dp_tune_ovrd_en is used to determine if the USB PHY driver will use
        software mapped TX EQ values for the DisplayPort Alt Mode use case when
        true. When false, the hardware default lookup table will be used.

        This node is rw. The value should be changed outside of a DisplayPort link
        to avoid a case where an override tune value is applied during link
        training but the default message bus teardown sequence is used during
        HPD_UNPLUG.
